}</script><section id="services-hero-532"><picture class="cs-bg-picture"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-55-4f108df2.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-55-13ca587e.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-55-fe8f9014.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-55-58519037.jpeg" height="775" width="1920" fetchpriority="high"></picture><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-card"><div class="cs-heading-group"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Las Cruces Landscaping Since 2005</span><h1 class="cs-title">Landscaping Services in <span class="cs-color">Las Cruces, NM</span></h1></div><p class="cs-text">Landscape design, hardscaping, irrigation, and xeriscaping built for the desert. 19 years of residential landscaping in Las Cruces, NM for homeowners across Doña Ana County.</p><div class="cs-button-group"><a class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a> <a class="cs-phone-button" href="tel:575-635-8883"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div></div></section><section id="services-intro-109"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern cs-fern-right"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern cs-fern-left"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-row"><picture class="cs-picture"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-56-aedfe927.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-56-57e8f719.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-56-19de36d9.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="Drought-tolerant landscape install in Las Cruces, NM" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-56-88ffe903.jpeg" height="456" width="480" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Why Las Cruces</span><h2 class="cs-title">Built for the Mesilla Valley</h2><p class="cs-text">Las Cruces is our home. We have spent 19 years building landscapes that do more than survive Doña Ana County’s desert climate. They thrive in it. From the adobe courtyards of Mesilla to the sloped lots of Picacho Hills and the modern homes of Sonoma Ranch, every property we touch is designed around the specific soil, sun, and monsoon patterns of this region.</p><p class="cs-text">Our crew is based right here in Las Cruces. We get on site fast, know which plants do well near the Organ Mountains, and understand the local permit process. No out-of-town contractors. No generic plant lists. Just landscaping in Las Cruces, NM tuned to the Chihuahuan Desert and the neighborhoods we have served for 19 years.</p><div class="cs-button-group"><a class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a> <a class="cs-phone-button" href="tel:575-635-8883"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="13" width="13" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div></div></div></section><section id="areas-services-610"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> What We Do Here</span><h2 class="cs-title">Las Cruces Landscaping Services</h2></div><div class="cs-grid"><ul class="cs-card-group"><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-landscape-design.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Landscape Design</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Custom plans built around Las Cruces sun, soil, HOA rules, and native plant options.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/landscape-design/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-landscaping.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Landscaping &amp; Install</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Full property planting, grading, and landscape rock installation for residential and commercial properties.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/landscaping/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-hardscaping.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Hardscaping &amp; Patios</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Flagstone, flagcrete, retaining walls, and patios built to handle the heat and monsoon runoff.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/hardscaping/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-xeriscaping.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Xeriscaping</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Low-water designs using Desert Willow, Agave, Red Yucca, and other Mesilla Valley natives that cut your water bill.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/landscaping/xeriscaping/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-irrigation.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Irrigation &amp; Sprinkler</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Drip systems and smart controllers sized for Las Cruces water rates and seasonal watering rules.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/irrigation/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-icon-wrap"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/icon-maintenance.svg" height="40" width="40" aria-hidden="true" loading="lazy"></div><h3 class="cs-item-title">Yard Maintenance</h3><p class="cs-item-text">Seasonal cleanup, pruning, and monsoon drainage checks for homes and businesses across Las Cruces.</p><a class="cs-item-link" href="/services/landscape-maintenance/">Learn More <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-up-right.svg" height="14" width="14" aria-hidden="true"></a></li></ul><aside class="cs-area-info"><h3 class="cs-area-title">One Call, One Crew, All Six Services</h3><p class="cs-area-text">Most Las Cruces properties need more than one service. Your xeriscape needs irrigation. Your patio needs drainage. Your design needs an install crew. One team handling everything keeps your project on time, on budget, and under one guarantee.</p><ul class="cs-area-bullets"><li><span class="cs-check" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" width="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M2 7.5 L5.5 11 L12 3.5"></path></svg> </span>Design-build under one roof</li><li><span class="cs-check" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" width="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M2 7.5 L5.5 11 L12 3.5"></path></svg> </span>Workmanship guarantee</li><li><span class="cs-check" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" width="14" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"><path d="M2 7.5 L5.5 11 L12 3.5"></path></svg> </span>Local office, local crew, fast response</li></ul></aside></div></div></section><section id="areas-landmarks-620"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-row"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Where We Work</span><h2 class="cs-title">Las Cruces Neighborhoods We Serve</h2><p class="cs-text">We cover every Las Cruces zip code: <strong>88001, 88005, 88007, 88011, and 88012</strong>. We also serve Mesilla, Doña Ana, Organ, Anthony, and Sunland Park. Near NMSU, White Sands National Park, or the Organ Mountains, every neighborhood has its own soil and sun conditions. We know them all.</p><div class="cs-button-group"><a class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a> <a class="cs-phone-button" href="tel:575-635-8883"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/phone.svg" height="13" width="13" aria-hidden="true"> (575) 635-8883</a></div></div><picture class="cs-picture"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-walkways-4-cf66c8c9.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-walkways-4-a32357af.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-walkways-4-a32357af.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="Stone walkway and landscape project in a Las Cruces neighborhood" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-walkways-4-5d4992c1.jpeg" height="773" width="580" loading="lazy"></picture></div><ul class="cs-neighborhoods"><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Sonoma Ranch <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88011</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Modern homes with strict HOA rules. We handle clean-lined hardscaping, native plantings, and the HOA approval paperwork.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Picacho Hills <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88007</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Estate lots on west-facing slopes. We build terraced retaining walls, control erosion, and design yards that keep your views open.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Mesilla Historic District <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88046</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Adobe courtyards and walled gardens near the Mesilla Plaza. Stone pathways, low-water natives, and traditional materials that match the village style.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">University Hills / NMSU <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88001</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">1960s to 1980s ranch homes near campus. We replace thirsty lawns with xeriscape, swap old shade trees, and upgrade aging irrigation.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Telshor / East Mesa <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88011</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Homes east of I-25 with heavy wind. We plant windbreaks, install gravel mulch, and rebuild drip zones that can handle the gusts.</p></li><li class="cs-neighborhood"><h3 class="cs-neighborhood-title">Organ Mountain Foothills <span class="cs-neighborhood-zip">88012</span></h3><p class="cs-neighborhood-text">Large desert lots near the Organs. Fire-wise plant choices, monsoon drainage grading, and landscape designs that work with the natural terrain.</p></li></ul></div></section><section id="services-why-353" class="cs-why-light"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper">Local Know-How</span><h2 class="cs-title">What Makes Las Cruces Landscaping Different</h2><p class="cs-intro">Las Cruces sits at 3,900 feet in the Chihuahuan Desert. That means hot, dry summers with 10 inches of rain per year, heavy monsoons from July through September, and caliche-heavy soils. Every design choice we make is shaped by those four facts.</p></div><div class="cs-gallery" aria-hidden="true"><picture class="cs-picture cs-picture-1"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-pavers-4-a1090985.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-pavers-4-092f8fe5.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-pavers-4-092f8fe5.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-pavers-4-7b257f17.jpeg" height="594" width="460" loading="lazy"></picture><picture class="cs-picture cs-picture-2"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-stone-borders-3-b25ef7c1.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-stone-borders-3-e2c41d47.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-stone-borders-3-e2c41d47.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-stone-borders-3-b6da701f.jpeg" height="439" width="330" loading="lazy"></picture></div><ul class="cs-feature-list"><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Caliche &amp; Alkaline Soil</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Las Cruces soil is mostly caliche hardpan and high-pH sand. We trench and amend to give roots room to grow, and we pick plants that actually like alkaline ground.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Monsoon Drainage</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Late-summer storms can drop an inch of rain in an hour. We grade every yard for positive drainage, use permeable hardscape materials, and size arroyos to protect your foundation.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Water Rules &amp; Rates</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">Las Cruces Utilities has seasonal watering schedules and tiered rates. Every irrigation system we install is set to the allowed days and early-morning hours. We size zones to keep you in the lowest pricing tier.</p></li><li class="cs-feature"><div class="cs-feature-head"><h3 class="cs-feature-title">Permits &amp; HOA Rules</h3><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" width="16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-feature-arrow"><path d="M4 12 L12 4"></path><path d="M6 4 L12 4 L12 10"></path></svg></div><p class="cs-feature-text">We pull permits through the Las Cruces Department of Community Development when retaining walls, drainage, or structures need them. We also know the Sonoma Ranch and Picacho Hills HOA rulebooks well.</p></li></ul><a class="cs-quote-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a></div></section><section id="testimonials-515" class="cs-reviews-carousel"><picture class="cs-bg-leaves"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/leaves-pattern-5f48081d.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/leaves-pattern-edeab06b.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/leaves-pattern-03e85c27.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/leaves-pattern-8329654d.jpeg" height="1072" width="1920" loading="lazy"></picture><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Testimonials</span><h2 class="cs-title">Let’s Talk About Your Outdoor Vision</h2></div><div class="cs-controls"><button class="cs-arrow cs-arrow-prev" aria-label="Previous reviews" type="button" data-reviews-prev=""><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M15 18l-6-6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></button> <button class="cs-arrow cs-arrow-next" aria-label="Next reviews" type="button" data-reviews-next=""><svg height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M9 6l6 6-6 6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></button></div></div><ul class="cs-card-group" data-reviews-track=""><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">David was incredibly knowledgeable and helpful. He patiently answered all of my questions about the plants and trees around my home and provided valuable insights into the issues I was facing. His friendly demeanor and expertise made the experience enjoyable and informative. I highly recommend him</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Alexis Silva</span> <span class="cs-role">a year ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/103948667181155023139/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">We had a great experience with David. We used him for one of our rental properties in Las Cruces and will definitely be using him again for the next one. Everything from start to finish was professional and timely. Highly recommend.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Travis Boyle</span> <span class="cs-role">a year ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/108997149124684397289/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">Brainard's Greenscapes recently revamped my backyard with rock landscaping. I couldn't be happier with how the project turned out. From start to finish David's team was professional, punctual, and courteous. They helped me select the the right materials and offered additional design ideas. The quality of work was EXCELLENT. I highly recommend David's team to all homeowners in Las Cruces looking for reliable landscaping company. The picture below is of my backyard 1 year later and there is still no weeds! I can't think Braindard's Greenscapes enough.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Matthew Lee</span> <span class="cs-role">a year ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/112275232644298872770/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">I had a sprinkler emergency and David came out immediately; found an effective solution to get me through until the major repairs could be made; and took care to make sure my house wasn't without water in the meantime. I am so grateful for his kindness and professionalism. He demonstrated considerable expertise and decisive decision making that got me through this emergencies with minimal stress. He is trustworthy and will be the first one I'll call on any future sprinkler needs.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">Jennifer Wees-Schkade</span> <span class="cs-role">2 years ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113879630740524577871/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li><li class="cs-item"><div class="cs-stars" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars" role="img"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/star-green.svg" height="18" width="18" aria-hidden="true"></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/quote-green.svg" height="51" width="51" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-quote-icon"><blockquote class="cs-item-text">Brainard’s Greenscapes is a top notch business. I have called on them on several occasions to fix issues with my irrigation system and for new projects. David, the owner, is a sincere, honest individual, who cares about his business and his customers. His employees are also kind and always professional. They are punctual and complete the job as promised and clean up after they are done. I am very pleased with David and his company and have recommended him to my neighbor, who is also a widow because I know he is honest and will not take advantage of her. David is a good guy and I recommend that you give him a call and see for yourself.</blockquote><div class="cs-item-footer"><div class="cs-author"><span class="cs-name">George Rodriguez</span> <span class="cs-role">6 years ago</span></div><a class="cs-google-link" href="https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/113926776793747685994/reviews" aria-label="View review on Google" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/google-g.svg" height="30" width="30"></a></div></li></ul></div></section><section id="areas-projects-630"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Case Studies</span><h2 class="cs-title">Las Cruces Project Showcase</h2></div><ul class="cs-project-group"><li class="cs-project"><picture class="cs-project-picture"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-40-67def9b1.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-40-02c85a24.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-40-214ff4b3.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="Sonoma Ranch modern desert landscape in Las Cruces, NM" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-xeriscaping-40-41777843.jpeg" height="411" width="616" loading="lazy"></picture><h3 class="cs-project-title">Sonoma Ranch Modern Oasis</h3><p class="cs-project-text">A full yard transformation with geometric hardscaping, landscape rock, and low-water native plants. Designed to meet HOA guidelines and cut water use by 60%.</p></li><li class="cs-project"><picture class="cs-project-picture"><source media="(max-width: 600px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-stone-borders-4-72a6847b.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(max-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-stone-borders-4-a1e43dae.webp" type="image/webp"><source media="(min-width: 1024px)" srcset="/assets/images/brainards-stone-borders-4-1e56a752.webp" type="image/webp"><img alt="Picacho Hills terraced stone border and retaining wall project" decoding="async" src="/assets/images/brainards-stone-borders-4-b22c6c68.jpeg" height="411" width="616" loading="lazy"></picture><h3 class="cs-project-title">Picacho Hills Terraced Retreat</h3><p class="cs-project-text">Stone retaining walls on a steep west-facing slope, with a viewing deck, drip irrigation, and native plantings that handle the afternoon sun.</p></li></ul></div></section><section id="faq-506"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/fern.svg" height="483" width="224" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-fern"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-content"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> FAQ</span><h2 class="cs-title">Las Cruces Landscaping FAQ</h2></div><ul class="cs-faq-list"><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Do you handle permits with the City of Las Cruces?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Yes. For retaining walls over 4 feet, large drainage changes, or structures on an easement, we pull permits through the Las Cruces Department of Community Development. We include that time in our proposal so there are no surprises.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">How much does landscaping cost in Las Cruces?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>It depends on the size of your yard, the materials, and the scope of work. A basic xeriscape conversion for a small front yard might start around a few thousand dollars. Larger projects with hardscaping, irrigation, and custom design cost more. We give free on-site estimates so you know the price before any work starts.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Which plants actually thrive in Las Cruces soil and heat?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Our go-to plants include Desert Willow, Chitalpa, Red Yucca, Agave parryi, Blue Grama grass, Mexican Feathergrass, and Texas Sage. All are cold-hardy to USDA zone 8a. They handle the Mesilla Valley’s alkaline caliche soils without special amendments. These are the best trees and shrubs for Las Cruces because they look great year-round and barely need watering once they are set.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">Do you work in HOA communities like Sonoma Ranch and Picacho Hills?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>Yes, regularly. We keep up with the approved plant lists, wall-height limits, and color rules for the major Las Cruces HOAs. We also fill out and submit the architectural review paperwork for you.</p></div></details></li><li class="cs-faq-item"><details class="cs-faq"><summary class="cs-faq-summary"><span class="cs-faq-question">When is the best time to install a new landscape in Las Cruces?</span> <span class="cs-faq-icon" aria-hidden="true"><svg height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="24"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2"></path></svg></span></summary><div class="cs-faq-body"><p>October through March is best. Cool weather lets plants grow strong roots before the 100°+ summer. We install year-round, but fall planting cuts first-year water use roughly in half compared to a spring install.</p></div></details></li></ul></div></section><section id="areas-stats-640"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><div class="cs-heading-col"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Our Coverage Area</span><h2 class="cs-title">Where We Work in Las Cruces</h2></div><div class="cs-copy-col"><p class="cs-text">The map below shows our core Las Cruces service area. We cover every residential and commercial zip code in the city, plus Mesilla, Doña Ana, Organ, Anthony, and Sunland Park.</p><a class="cs-button-solid cs-nav-button" href="/contact/">Schedule an Estimate</a></div></div><div class="cs-map" aria-label="Map of Las Cruces, NM service area"><iframe allowfullscreen="" height="430" loading="lazy" referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade" src="https://www.google.com/maps?q=Las+Cruces+NM&amp;output=embed" title="Map of Las Cruces, NM service area" width="1280"></iframe></div><ul class="cs-stats"><li class="cs-stat"><span class="cs-stat-number">500+</span> <span class="cs-stat-label">Las Cruces Projects</span></li><li class="cs-stat"><span class="cs-stat-number">20+</span> <span class="cs-stat-label">Years in the Valley</span></li><li class="cs-stat"><span class="cs-stat-number">5/5</span> <span class="cs-stat-label">Average Rating</span></li><li class="cs-stat"><span class="cs-stat-number">100%</span> <span class="cs-stat-label">Quality Guarantee</span></li></ul></div></section><section id="areas-neighbors-660"><div class="cs-container"><div class="cs-header"><span class="cs-topper"><span class="cs-topper-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/arrow-right.svg" height="10" width="48" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-topper-arrow"> Nearby</span><h2 class="cs-title">Neighboring Areas We Serve</h2><p class="cs-text">We also handle landscape projects in nearby Mesilla Valley communities just minutes away.</p></div><ul class="cs-neighbors"><li class="cs-neighbor"><a class="cs-neighbor-link" href="/service-areas/mesilla-nm/"><span class="cs-neighbor-name">Landscaping in Mesilla, NM</span><span class="cs-neighbor-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li><li class="cs-neighbor"><a class="cs-neighbor-link" href="/service-areas/mesilla-park-nm/"><span class="cs-neighbor-name">Landscaping in Mesilla Park, NM</span><span class="cs-neighbor-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li><li class="cs-neighbor"><a class="cs-neighbor-link" href="/service-areas/dona-ana-nm/"><span class="cs-neighbor-name">Landscaping in Doña Ana, NM</span><span class="cs-neighbor-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li><li class="cs-neighbor"><a class="cs-neighbor-link" href="/service-areas/sonoma-ranch-nm/"><span class="cs-neighbor-name">Landscaping in Sonoma Ranch, NM</span><span class="cs-neighbor-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span></a></li></ul></div></section><section id="lets-talk-318"><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-tree.svg" height="457" width="427" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-tree"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-1.svg" height="20" width="64" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-1"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-2.svg" height="15" width="56" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-2"> <img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-bird-3.svg" height="15" width="46" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-bird cs-bird-3"><div class="cs-container"><h2 class="cs-title">Let’s Talk About Your Las Cruces Landscape</h2><a class="cs-talk-button" href="/contact/">Get a Free Estimate</a></div><img alt="" decoding="async" src="/assets/svgs/talk-grass-top.svg" aria-hidden="true" class="cs-grass"></section>
